        "Id": "mechdef_sunder_SD1-X1",
        "Name": "Sunder",
        "Details": "The product of what was learned from captured Loki and Thor OmniMechs, the Sunder is the assault class 'Mech of the Draconis Combine's first generation of Inner Sphere OmniMechs. Much like Avatar, the Sunder stems from Combine engineers efforts to re-engineer captured Clan OmniMechs for manufacture, selecting examples of the Loki and Thor to embody an assault class design. The Combine engineers rightly determined the legs of both progenitor designs could easily support twenty extra tons, but while the internal frame was able to accommodate the extra weight the leg actuators of prototype Sunders burned out at an alarmingly rapid rate, forcing significant rework with more robust versions. The Sunder weighs ninety tons and uses a Hermes 360 XL engine to save weight while giving the 'Mech a top speed of 65 km/h, the bulky engine forcing the designers to move the torso OmniPod bays above the cockpit. The 'Mech carries two Large Lasers for its primary long-range weapons. For short-range engagements, the Sunder has an Autocannon/20 that comprises the bulk of its firepower. This is supported by two medium lasers and a trio of SRM-4 launchers, making the Sunder prime most lethal at short ranges.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
